        155,
        515,
        167
      ]
    },
    {
      "line_1based": 9,
      "serial_label": "L9",
      "text": "[The Spanish ambassador in Rabat has admitted that some assistance to the Moroccan tribes may have come from local Spanish sources, but he has denied that Spain intends to make war on Morocco.]",
      "char_len": 193,
      "line_kind": "text_line",
      "line_box_xyxy": [
        6,
        175,
        515,
        185
      ]
    },
    {
      "line_1based": 10,
      "serial_label": "L10",
      "text": "",
      "char_len": 0,
      "line_kind": "text_line",
      "line_box_xyxy": [
        6,
        193,
        515,
        203
      ]
    },
    {
      "line_1based": 11,
      "serial_label": "L11",
      "text": "[The Spanish military governor of Melilla, one of five tiny Spanish-controlled points in northern Morocco, is reported to have granted asylum to Berber leader Lahcen Lyoussi, a former crown counselor who is being sought by government forces for involvement in tribal dissidence.]",
